title: Border, 2010-31-345, 1872–1900
provenance: Donor purchased the two Grantil sample books from a private collector in France ca. 2000. For the remaining non-Grantil pieces, the French, Belgian and English papers were acquired from various sources in Europe, while the American samples were acquired from private collections in the United States.
medium: Machine-printed in oil colors with engraved copper rollers
description: Sanitary paper with alternating motifs of flowers on stems, narrow band at top and wider band across bottom. Printed in shades of brown on tan ground.
inscribed: Printed on recto at bottom edge: Washable
